\[ \sum_{i=1}^{n} i r^i = 
\frac{n r^{n+2} - (n+1)r^{n+1} + r}{(1-r)^2} .\]$BR $BR
Now consider the series  \( \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \, n  r^n \). $BR $BR
\(  \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \, n  r^n = \)
\{ans_rule(40)\}$BR

EOT

&ANS(std_num_str_cmp(0, ['INF', 'MINF', 'DIV']));
